She turned to an empty page and noted the date. Below, she wrote "11.5.648–13.12.648".
"Are you refreshing old memories?" Ivory asked and looked at the old notebook. Kari nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? It's only a few days away now."
Kari knocked twice on the lantern. "No," as Ivory had suspected. The Ice King never allowed Kari to leave because he considered her a "blemish." She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family, while her siblings were all boys.
Similar things applied to Ivory too. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed as though the world was changing around her. As punishment for this difference, Ivory was given tasks where she spent most of the time alone.
In addition, Ivory was also forced to serve the princess. But it didn't matter much to Ivory because she gained a friend in the process.
“You have a birthday coming up, right?” asked Ivory, thinking about how the princess would have a birthday in a few days. Kari nodded with a sad spark in her light blue eyes.
“Do you want to celebrate your birthday?” asked Ivory, remembering the last time the princess had answered this question.
“No,” said Kari. Ivory knew that this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother banished. Ivory was just a baby at the time, but she remembered how upset the servants and the city's residents were. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen and that she could even predict things that would actually happen.
“Well, what do you want to do?” asked Ivory. Kari looked excitedly at Ivory. She held a piece of paper in her hand. On it was written:
15 x 15 cm Canvas
Weiß, verschiedene Blautöne
Pinsel in sechs verschiedenen Größen
Staffelei
„These things should I get for you?“, Ivory asked the silent princess whose pigtails swung back and forth with her vigorous knocking. „Yes?“ Ivory giggled softly. The usually reserved princess showed such enthusiasm. It was the first time she had asked about something that wasn't related to books and came from outside her room.
„Okay! See you later?“, asked Ivory, stood up, and slinked through the chaos of papers and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her bed blanket.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess had finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things beyond her reach, like Malfarben.
Ivory walked through the hallways again and tried to ignore the gossiping maidservants.
“I heard she is possessed by Queen Eirwen and therefore keeps going to this room repeatedly.”
“I heard she eats children in this room.”
“She looks like a man, isn't that not normal?”
Ivory covered her ears because she simply couldn't ignore the chatter and continued walking. The chamber of the royal painter was in the east wing behind the second door on the left side.
Ivory approached the door, which was just as intricately decorated as Karis' door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six Urdragons supposedly created by Frostfell. For a history-loving painter, the presence of the White Dragon on the door made perfect sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual chaos. Splatters of paint everywhere, brushes and papers scattered throughout the room, easels covering every inch of the wall. Unexpectedly, however, another scene presented itself. The entire space was clean, and a chair stood against a background of red silk. On the chair sat Crown Prince Aquilo, who was being painted in a portrait.
“Good morning, Ivory! Do you want to watch your future king being painted?” asked Aquilo and winked at Ivory.
“Excuse me, Little Prince,” said Ivory, ignoring him largely and gathering the things that the silent Princess wished for. “I am only here to get Malsachen.”
“My little girl wants to leave already?” asked Aquilo. “But I want you to stay!”
“Not me,” said Ivory, finding the Malsachen on the list and putting them in a box. “Besides, I am not a girl.”
The prince, however, had a different opinion. “Oh sweetie, that's just a phase! As you grow older, you'll get over it!” he said vaguely.
I have to go, said Ivory, feeling uncomfortable by the prince's response. And Ivory remembered all the ugly remarks he and others had made about her gender identity in the past. I just want to be away from here.
„You're leaving already?“ Suddenly, the prince appeared at the door and ignored the loud objections of the royal painter.
„That's no behavior for a future king!“, said Ivory.
„No one will find out. People won't believe it and the painter will keep quiet if his life means anything to him.“ He glanced at the painter briefly and then leaned closer to Ivory. „What do you think about a date?“ Ivory had been harassed several times in the past, but never by a prince, let alone the crown prince.
„Do you even know what the word 'no' means?“, Ivory spat out and pushed the crown prince away from her.
„No“, answered Aquilo with a smile. Of course, the crown prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word "no" means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. „Why do you want to go out with someone like me? You must have around 100 admirers, right?“
„Actually, there are 50,“ he interrupted Ivory, still smiling. He threw back his hair, which whipped around in the cold air.
„Get it through your head now! Why me? I'm a threat to the palace.“ Ivory crossed her arms.
„You are the most beautiful girl I have ever seen.“ Aquilo lifted Ivory's chin with his finger and forced her to look at him.
